snippet: As Greece tries to secure the next installment from its $92 billion package, Greek officials and foreign creditors remain at odds over whether Athens has met economic overhaul targets.
abstract: Greek officials and country's foreign creditors, despite negotiations, cannot agree on international bailout terms, resulting in delayed release of next payout of rescue funds.

byline.contributor: James Kanter contributed reporting from Brussels.

lead_paragraph: As Greece tries to secure the next installment from its $92 billion package, Greek officials and foreign creditors remain at odds over whether Athens has met economic overhaul targets.

headline.main: Creditors Withhold 2 Billion Euro Bailout Payment From Greece
headline.print_headline: Creditors Delay Release of Greek Bailout Funds
